## Branching Strategy
- main: always releasable
- develop (optional): integration branch
- feature/*, bugfix/*, hotfix/* per ticket

## Commits
- Conventional commits: feat, fix, docs, refactor, test, chore
- Small, atomic commits tied to tickets

## PRs
- Keep PRs focused; <300 lines of reviewable changes when possible
- Include context, screenshots (UI), and test plan

## Releases and Versioning
- Use Semantic Versioning (https://semver.org)
- Tag releases with `vMAJOR.MINOR.PATCH`
- Maintain `CHANGELOG.md` (Keep a Changelog)
- Automate changelog and release tagging in CI where feasible

## Validation Checklist
- [ ] Branch named with ticket key and type
- [ ] Commit messages conventional and meaningful
- [ ] PR small, focused, with test plan

